  "author_association": "NONE",
  "body": "*Title*: Document the default value of buffer configuration setting `max_request_bytes`\r\n\r\n*Description*:\r\n\r\nConfiguration parameter `max_request_bytes` can be tweaked to increase the size of the buffer to workaround a HTTP Response Status Code [413](https://httpstatuses.com/413) `Payload Too Large` [RFC 7231]. \r\n\r\nThere is no information what is the default value in envoy documentations either for [v1-api](https://www.envoyproxy.io/docs/envoy/v1.8.0/api-v1/http_filters/buffer_filter#config-http-filters-buffer-v1) (version 1.8.0) nor [v2-api](https://www.envoyproxy.io/docs/envoy/v1.11.0/api-v2/config/filter/http/buffer/v2/buffer.proto#envoy-api-msg-config-filter-http-buffer-v2-buffer) (latest version 1.12.0).  \r\n\r\nFor lot of configuration parameters envoy documentation explicit the default values. An example on the [Circuit breaker settings](https://www.envoyproxy.io/docs/envoy/latest/api-v2/api/v2/cluster/circuit_breaker.proto.html?highlight=max_requests#cluster-circuitbreakers-thresholds) \r\n\r\nI tried to figured out what is the default value for that `max_request_bytes` parameter by investigating the code in several places [protocol buffer definition](https://github.com/envoyproxy/envoy/blob/master/api/envoy/config/filter/http/buffer/v2/buffer.proto#L23), [cpp BufferFilter object definition](https://github.com/envoyproxy/envoy/blob/master/source/extensions/filters/http/buffer/buffer_filter.h#L28) and [test samples](https://github.com/envoyproxy/envoy/blob/master/test/config/integration/server.yaml#L274). \r\n\r\nWould you mind to let me know if I have missed some parts in the documentation which would give me more details or if it's still unspecified.\r\n\r\n*Relevant Links*:\r\n[V1 API HTTP Filters Buffer](https://www.envoyproxy.io/docs/envoy/v1.8.0/api-v1/http_filters/buffer_filter#config-http-filters-buffer-v1) documentation link\r\n[V2 API HTTP Filters Buffer](https://www.envoyproxy.io/docs/envoy/latest/api-v2/config/filter/http/buffer/v2/buffer.proto#envoy-api-msg-config-filter-http-buffer-v2-buffer) documentation link\r\n",
